		September 1, 2010 at 9:25 am</a>
        		 
		</div>
		<p>Interesting how Cory sometimes reverts to examples of scarce goods when trying to bolster his arguments; bits are not scarce, and they only become artificially so when DRM is used. Isn&#8217;t he anti-DRM?</p>
<p><a href="http://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2009/04/doctorows-law" rel="nofollow">http://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2009/04/doctorows-law</a></p>
<p>Why does Cory want to put a lock on culture??  <img src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
		</div>
