		<p>Cory asked me to reinsert some edited bits, which I just did (he approved the first edit on the run, and had second thoughts upon a second reading). So have another look to see if his arguments now address the scarce/non-scarce issues. I think his argument is: &#8220;property restrictions are made-up concepts we apply to rivalrous goods for socially beneficial reasons, so why not apply similar concepts to non-rivalrous goods too?&#8221;</p>
