		<p>Thanks. I&#8217;m not attached to trademark; it&#8217;s part of the existing legal regime we can use, but that doesn&#8217;t mean it shouldn&#8217;t be replaced with something better. I support any and all IP reform, but meaningful IP reform is unlikely to happen in my lifetime. It&#8217;s what we can do right now, in this world, with the tools at hand, that interests me more.</p>
<p>Oh, and what I&#8217;d do about the Yes Men? Nothing. I&#8217;m only interested in addressing fraud, not satire. Same with kids scrawling trademarks for fun: that&#8217;s not fraud. </p>
