		<p>My mind always reverts to the reality that copyright (all copyright) is built for the rich amongst us.</p>
<p>You must both admit the basic expense of acquiring any sort of copyright for anything is notmally beyond the grasp of your average musician, inventor or fine visual artist. Vague copyright concepts such as &#8220;Creative Commons&#8221; (what exactly is it?!) and now &#8220;Creator Endorsed Mark&#8221; (ooh, goody! how hip!)<br />
only leave me with many bad tastes in my mouth.</p>
